This paper deals with detecting side-channel vulnerabilities in software, which is a topic related to computer security (cs.CR). The approach presented in the paper involves using fuzzing to analyze program behavior, which is a technique commonly used in software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also discusses implementation details for Java programs, which falls under programming languages (cs.PL). The methodology presented in the paper can be applied to any language, which suggests a systems focus (cs.SY). Finally, the paper uses heuristics to guide the fuzzing process, which involves machine learning techniques (cs.LG).
